- gate-puppet-nova-puppet-unit-4.0 http://logs.openstack.org/11/186511/1/check/gate-puppet-nova-puppet-unit-4.0/6cb9fd9/ : FAILURE in 9m 44s (non-voting)
- gate-puppet-nova-puppet-beaker-rspec-dsvm-trusty http://logs.openstack.org/11/186511/1/check/gate-puppet-nova-puppet-beaker-rspec-dsvm-trusty/8eaf4d5/ : SUCCESS in 15m 38s (non-voting)
- gate-puppet-nova-puppet-beaker-rspec-dsvm-centos7 http://logs.openstack.org/11/186511/1/check/gate-puppet-nova-puppet-beaker-rspec-dsvm-centos7/ab8466f/ : SUCCESS in 17m 04s (non-voting)
- gate-puppet-nova-puppet-syntax-future http://logs.openstack.org/11/186511/1/check/gate-puppet-nova-puppet-syntax-future/bb24499/ : SUCCESS in 6m 16s'}, {'account_id': 7156, 'date': '2015-05-28 18:24:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

AFAIK, we have (as far) reserved package_ensure for OpenStack packages.

We are now introducing new behavior:
- package_ensure now manages non-openstack packages
- nova_package_ensure parameter which is not a pattern found elsewhere

So I feel concerned about this change of behavior and consistency. I would be fine if only package_ensure (for nova package), libvirt_package_ensure (for libvirt package) were introduced and pick wasn't used."}, {'account_id': 7156, 'date': '2015-05-28 18:25:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

-1 because of my concern, not worth -2 though.'}, {'account_id': 10540, 'date': '2015-05-28 19:00:20.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I'm ok with changing it.  The logic for why I did it the way it is, is that we generally set all of these to 'latest' to make upgrades easier.  We handle versioning of repos external to these modules.  With the above approach we just have to set one variable to latest, not two."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-05-28 19:08:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Build succeeded (check-tripleo pipeline).

- check-tripleo-ironic-overcloud-f20puppet-nonha http://logs.openstack.org/11/186511/1/check-tripleo/check-tripleo-ironic-overcloud-f20puppet-nonha/80a8f22/ : SUCCESS in 1h 17m 28s'}, {'account_id': 7156, 'date': '2015-05-28 19:46:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I agree with you that having one value to set is very convenient.

Unfortunately, although you can upgrade libvirt just "fine", it's not true for all packages. For example, updating the iSCSI package on a compute node will drop all iSCSI sessions. I learned it the hard way after I set "latest" to all the packages managed by Puppet.

So I would like the option to be a "strong" opt-in which does not conflict with the actual expected package_ensure behavior and "non-written" convention we had and that I enforced in multiple past changes. And which won't require any exception in the future due to the nature of the package.'}, {'account_id': 9060, 'date': '2015-05-29 03:59:20.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

(1 comment)

I'd like to see a little more explanation of the package_ensure parameter, as suggested in comments.  Otherwise I like it.  I don't feel like it needs to be any more strongly opt-in, especially since it defaults to just 'present.'"}, {'account_id': 7156, 'date': '2015-06-01 22:17:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Do we really need to manage libvirt package state?

I feel it should be managed by a dedicated Puppet module, we (puppet-nova) are not in the business of managing libvirt itself or any other hypervisors.

Furthermore, the nova-compute-libvirt package already depends on:
- libvirt-bin (Ubuntu)
- libvirt-daemon-system (Debian)
- libvirt-daemon-kvm (RedHat)

So there is no reason for us to explicitly install the libvirt daemon.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-06-29 23:06:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified-1

Merge Failed.

This change was unable to be automatically merged with the current state of the repository. Please rebase your change and upload a new patchset.'}, {'account_id': 10540, 'date': '2015-12-07 21:59:29.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Allow configuring libvirt package ensures

This patch will allow the user to override the package ensure value from
the default of 'present'.  It can be specified for all packages via the
`package_ensure` parameter, or use the libvirt and nova specific
overrides.

Change-Id: I99e8f4a4372f48074b037422eaf0ab0b2d65f58a

commit_message:
Move keystonemiddleware to use the same ACLs as keystoneauth

After discussing this with steve martinelli (PTL), it makes sense to
move the keystonemiddleware core ACLs to have the same group that
really focuses on keystoneauth. This is because both keystoneauth
and keystonemiddleware are mostly looked at by a slightly more
specialized group.

Keystone-core group still has full rights to vote on the project. This
allows for an expanded set of eyes who focus more on authz within
openstack to be involved with keystonemiddleware.

Change-Id: If56f5b7636a6880f61ac9510f2bff546b7c2bf4b

commit_message:
Remove XML tags from .ini section in identity/domains.rst

in f60d7239, the file security-guide-rst/source/identity/domains.rst
was added with an ini section using domain_specific_drivers_enabled
and domain_config_dir config values, both with some XML tags.
Probably those were a copy/paste mistake, given that the file
security-guide/section_identity-domains.xml was added in the same
commit and has the exact same lines.

Change-Id: I2e91fda0e2fae02097004f80d6bcc1c93807b314

commit_message:
scenario003: fix tempest path

In 6d26ea258fdfa5677c99f107eace9936a8e168c0 we wanted to do aregulart
clone of tempest and we made sure the path was /tmp/openstack/tempest -
but we missed to update the path in ::tempest Puppet class.

This patch fix it.

Change-Id: Ie0bc6c6ad887898234870d44b77a80d4b65a5419

commit_message:
Update vexxhost to Identity v3

There is a discovery URL for vexxhost for keystone v3. Also, there is a
new vexxhost domain for it. Also, vexxhost has DNS running designate v1.
And make the region list a list of one region, because there is a second
region coming soon.

Change-Id: Ie72c19976646f41c713124659e69725df59e1580

commit_message:
set `is_admin` on tokens for admin project

Adds two new configuration value:

admin_project_name
admin_project_domain_name

If both values are set, and tokens requested for
projects (only, not domains) that match both will have an
additional value in them;  `is_admin_project=true`

DocImpact
-- Configuration changes need documentation
APIImpact
-- Adds optional return values in token validation calls
SecurityImpact
-- Should be helpful in making access control decisions

Implements: blueprint is-admin-project
Partial-Bug: #968696

Change-Id: Ic9cf9862739381a30130b4be87075f726736ff88

commit_message:
Add support for generalized per-region settings

Internap creates a public and a private network for each customer for
each region on region activation. This means there is a per-region
external network that the user may want to specify. Also, conoha has
per-region auth-urls. Per-region config is still
overridden by argparse or kwargs values.

Change-Id: Ie2f3d2ca3ccbe7e3dd674983136b42c323544997

commit_message:
Remove py26 support

As of mitaka, the infra team won't have the resources available to
reasonably test py26, also the oslo team is dropping py26 support
from their libraries. sine we rely on oslo for a lot of our work,
and depend on infra for our CI, we should drop py26 support too.
Closes-Bug: 1519510

Change-Id: I4997706a854e3a0e761776dbf0609e556c1d803d

commit_message:
Fixing unit tests after removal from Horizon

Our code was still pointing at openstack_dashboard.
test rather than sahara_dashboard.test.  This patch
should fix that and allow our tests to start passing
again.  Also adding a requirement for netifaces.

Change-Id: Icea05e4cf3c55937a4b84728cc6ef63e6c944080

commit_message:
Invoke tox rpm-packaging-lint for PR checks

To have more than noop gating, we'd like to run the
"lint" tox environment on check and gate of each review.

Change-Id: I8f3a9817d29e2321f9eaf21f8e7974dea86e8960

The logic of this patch is wrong. You cannot allow retype between different extra_specs as long as you don't add support for migration between backends, for instance, along with all other things that an extra_specs change would entail.  
Please check the original patch to support retyping for QoS changes only (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/135874/) and you'll see that it is necessary to ensure that the volume types only differ in their QoS settings. (That's also why https://review.openstack.org/#/c/243537/ is necessary to correct the comparison.)"}, {'account_id': 15961, 'date': '2015-11-13 08:54:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

RBD.retype is not called directly. Please see Zhiteng's comments at your patch: 

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/243537/

All the checks have been done before calling retype in driver."}, {'account_id': 15961, 'date': '2015-11-13 08:56:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

With the former check in volume.manager, extra_specs has nothing impact in rbd backend.

Before rbd.retype is called, encryption and host have
been checked so that encryptions are different and
host are same.
Meanwhile, as extra_spec is not used during the
rbd driver. As a result, even if they are different
rbd.retype can still return True which means no need
to do further migration.

'}, {'created': '2015-11-18 05:30:52.000000000', 'message': 'Delete unused codes in rbd.retype

Before rbd.retype is called, encryption and host have
been checked so that encryptions are different and
host are same.
Meanwhile, as extra_spec is not used during the
rbd driver. As a result, even if they are different
rbd.retype can still return True which means no need
to do further migration.

DocImpact

commit_message:
Delete unused codes in rbd.retype

Before rbd.retype is called, encryption and host have
been checked so that encryptions are different and
host are same.
Meanwhile, as extra_spec is not used during the
rbd driver. As a result, even if they are different
rbd.retype can still return True which means no need
to do further migration.

Change-Id: Id025a51631676389203b8e3892a5826c834105ca
Closes-Bug: #1515493
Closes-Bug: #1514775

commit_message:
Add PyKMIP test asserts

This change adds two low-level asserts that test PyKMIP Enumeration
object values. These asserts were previously removed to account for
an update to the PyKMIP library. These asserts have been updated to
work with the new library version. See commit c6e806bb78 for more
information.

Change-Id: I333032f4b468bfd4d465291c7955cefcebbf9bdd

commit_message:
Allow distro packages to install dependencies, etc

This patch updates init.pp so that it only attempts to
install the mistral package (which should create the
user, group, and install all the required dependencies
itself).

Includes tests for each supported OS Family.

Change-Id: I3f996cddb5ff31431545e2f8e4a376fccc2eda61

commit_message:
Fix keystone configuration.

This patch updates the mistral keystone_authtoken configuration
to be inline with other OpenStack puppet modules. Specifically
it adds a unique setting for identity_uri so that it can
be set correctly rather than re-using auth_uri for both
settings.

Includes some new tests for these settings.

Change-Id: I092516aa07f6dec4cb26e44182f125d27c8ff334

commit_message:
Ironic doesn't use cacert while talking to Swift

Current we have a keystonemiddleware.auth_token.cafile
which is used for talking to Openstack services using https.
Ironic doesn't pass this down to swiftclient for verifying
https connections.

Closes-Bug: 1454353
Change-Id: Id085ea6c0f1d072ec631b9851ddfde96852aca56

commit_message:
Cap astroid to unbreak pylint.

While projects run different versions of pylint, astroid which is a pylint
dependency has done an API breaking point release - 1.4.{0,1} breaks pylint
1.4.4.

Since this is a stable branch, I'm just capping everything, we have no
expectation of projects in stable branches revising their pylint versions.

Upstream bug url: https://bitbucket.org/logilab/astroid/issues/275/140-and-141-fail-to-work-with-pylint-144

Change-Id: Iaf2c5dbb92cacbc236083f8f6926a426bfb28f21

commit_message:
Do not pass auth token into virtual media floppy

Deploy ramdisk in agent based drivers uses lookup and heartbeat which
are part of public ACL. Auth token is not required to be passed into
virtual media floppy during deploy for agent_ilo driver.

Reason to backport:
Passing auth token unnecessarily for the APIs where it is not
required could cause security issue depending on the deploy setup.

(cherry picked from commit Ice85ae4bb84d2f7c53759264812e5fbc29ac510f)

The cherry-picked commit Ice85ae4bb84d2f7c53759264812e5fbc29ac510f
removes auth token for both iscsi_ilo and agent_ilo drivers as all
the vendorpassthru methods called by deploy ramdisk are changed to
public ACL.
In Juno branch only lookup and heartbeat methods are into
public ACL list. The code for preparing floppy image is common to
both iscsi_ilo and agent_ilo drivers.
The cherry-picked commit has been modified to ensure that auth token
is passed to virtual media floppy image only when it is being called
for iscsi_ilo driver.

Change-Id: I86b4dbdbe03220d2dde46d4a98e3b31aabf2f6bf
Closes-Bug: #1518560

Swift containers and objects that were created by a particular
SwiftSignalHandle should be deleted when the resource is deleted.

=== AND ===

Handle 404 and 409 response when deleting containers

Attempting to delete a stack with multiple SwiftSignalHandles will result
in a 409 error from Swift due to a logic error in the SwiftSignalHandle
resource. This change ensures that we properly handle 404 and 409
responses when deleting Swift containers.

commit_message:
Add a handle_delete method to SwiftSignalHandle

Swift containers and objects that were created by a particular
SwiftSignalHandle should be deleted when the resource is deleted.

Change-Id: Id9df03e139ca0632996f4f66c5f39e27bb04d1fb
Closes-Bug: #1379040
Closes-Bug: #1392867
(cherry picked from commit d8dc9a8b9ed1bc6949c12cdd7b4fea3a0f4d8470
                       and 0c284f7debb1b5175bb2f5693a5488f6fa49b19d)

[{'created': '2015-11-17 05:54:25.000000000', 'message': "Copy the env to the backup stack in failed update

When an update fails, we currently update the environment of the stack
to contain both the new and old parameters and types. Unfortunately we
don't do that for the backup stack which is reused. This patch adds the
environment change.

Change-Id: I4dc5dd35e4aeee498dd8960a1000913e97b924d5
Closes-Bug: 1508096

commit_message:
Copy the env to the backup stack in failed update

When an update fails, we currently update the environment of the stack
to contain both the new and old parameters and types. Unfortunately we
don't do that for the backup stack which is reused. This patch adds the
environment change.

Change-Id: I4dc5dd35e4aeee498dd8960a1000913e97b924d5
Closes-Bug: 1508096
(cherry picked from commit 88da460316e2c18b3ceb58f51dcf0bda717a18a3)

commit_message:
Support time-delays in server.resize

Resize operation in nova(that we are for flavor update) is
asynchronous. So the server may be ACTIVE when we are checking
server-resize operations(not RESIZE as was excepted).
We need to wait for a while till the server becomes RESIZE.

The patch add support of this case to Server resource in heat.
Closes-bug: #1471135

Change-Id: I19914081996104c5f2144a6de795173f26774c21
(cherry picked from commit 274f96b8e51ba04d5c1230c0fa3aa8066b24901e)

commit_message:
Pass the resource name into get_resource_info()

Problem
If you have the following in the environment, the resource "a_res" will
be created with "other.yaml" instead of "my.yaml".

resource_registry:
  resources:
    a_res:
      OS::Nova::Server: my.yaml
  OS::Nova::Server: other.yaml

The reason for this is that the resource name has not been passed into
get_resource_info().

Note: a functional test is coming in a later commit.

Closes-bug: 1418935
Change-Id: I45a453ac342eab287544fc9d4f94e9bd5716bb8e
(cherry picked from commit 92669014ea5729c137e18751b97ab14229c65b0e)

some rest api modules to be used by ryu plugin were removed.

'}, {'created': '2015-11-03 00:43:08.000000000', 'message': 'Specify the default v3.25 to RYU_BRANCH in case of the ryu plugin

Currently RYU_BRANCH variable is definded in stackrc by default master
and it is used by both ofagent and ryu plugin.
But in the latest version(3.26 and later) of ryu library, some rest
api modules to be used by ryu plugin were removed.
So we use refs/tags/v3.25 as default branch in the case of ryu plugin.

Change-Id: Ie244f610260560d8efb2fb54ef3ecbb7e11968b7
Closes-Bug: 1505561
'}, {'created': '2015-11-04 01:48:28.000000000', 'message': 'Specify the default v3.25 to RYU_BRANCH in case of the ryu plugin

Currently RYU_BRANCH variable is definded in stackrc by default master
and it is used by both ofagent and ryu plugin.
But in the latest version(3.26 and later) of ryu library, some rest
api modules to be used by ryu plugin were removed.
So we use refs/tags/v3.25 as default branch in the case of ryu plugin.

commit_message:
Specify the default v3.25 to RYU_BRANCH in case of the ryu plugin

Currently RYU_BRANCH variable is definded in stackrc by default master
and it is used by both ofagent and ryu plugin.
But in the latest version(3.26 and later) of ryu library, some rest
api modules to be used by ryu plugin were removed.
So we use refs/tags/v3.25 as default branch in the case of ryu plugin.

Change-Id: Ie244f610260560d8efb2fb54ef3ecbb7e11968b7
Closes-Bug: #1505561

commit_message:
Stack resources table improvement

In spite of the fact that status of stack resource is "Create complete",
the row color remains yellow instead of grey. This patch set keeps the
column for detailed states and adds a new hidden column for correct
states displaying.

Closes-Bug: #1385244

Change-Id: I2a9e5a6f456378dcd1f96d96f69fdba1527e4f25
(cherry picked from commit 6934660945e589b595c3a53179064488d25c4079)

commit_message:
Tidy up notification_driver implementation across projects

The various os_* roles implement the notification driver in
the config files in a number of different ways.

This commit standardises the implementation.

Some of the decisions that were made here (remove the variables for
the driver altogether, do not configure notifications at all if not
ceilometer) are based on an irc discussion and the outcomes.

The following variables have been removed:
 - glance_ceilometer_notification_driver
 - glance_notification_driver
 - neutron_notification_driver

If these items need to be set differently, the config_override
facility may be used.

UpgradeImpact
Bug: #1522506
Change-Id: I1ac7648a545c35f8f77d79f9cb0d9021bdb9e653
(cherry picked from commit 24488f45c66ed29f8c3c4d370e740af325964508)

commit_message:
Handle os.listdir failures in object-updater

While investigating bug 1375348 I discovered the problem
reported there was not limited to the object-auditor.  The
object-updater has similar bugs.

This patch catches the unhandled exception that can be thrown
by os.listdir if the self.devices directory is inaccessible.

Change-Id: I6293b840916bb63cf9eebbc05068d9a3c871bdc3
Related-bug: 1375348
(cherry picked from commit 1c9bc0b522bed333b04a46ed7bd2c66a4eb89860)

commit_message:
Handle os.listdir failures in container-updater

While investigating bug 1375348 I discovered the problem
reported there was not limited to the object-auditor.  The
container-updater has similar bugs.

This patch catches the unhandled exception that can be thrown by
os.listdir.

Change-Id: I7eed122bf6b663e6e7894ace136b6f4653db4985
Related-bug: 1375348
(cherry picked from commit d895cea07f4f51b7d3e683344729a08e76f85f51)

commit_message:
Make "VLAN", "VXLAN" and "GRE" translatable

VLAN has been translated in other places.  Use the translation in
create network and make sure all 3 are translatable.

Change-Id: I2263d1ceef1e4aa6fe1c324e0a9ad5a66fa1d714
Closes-bug: #1381679
(cherry picked from commit 2db3f5ecab1e72fea53ed5456ca02dd70ab73052)

commit_message:
Reauthenticate on token expiration

Add new config option reauthentication_auth_plugin
for enforce usage of trusts_auth_plugin for making
authenticated requests.
Also add stale_token_duration option for determing
time in seconds before token expiration for considering
such token as about to expire.
Try to get new token if old token is about to expire.
Add reauthentication for stack create/update actions.

Change-Id: Id7d6692128964f4ef35762d43ef2738df0d83f4b
Co-Authored-By: Steven Hardy <shardy@redhat.com>
Closes-Bug: #1306294
(cherry picked from commit 33bf717bbcdbdf5db47dc54f10ed1e33fdb0e5c9)

It wouldn't be good to merge this and then watch the overall success rate for Neutron at the gate decrease."}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2015-12-07 15:40:42.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2015-12-07 15:43:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

Are you certain? There are a number of jobs in the check queue for neutron that vote, that are not in the gate queue'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-12-07 16:02:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-project-config-layout http://logs.openstack.org/74/205674/6/check/gate-project-config-layout/ee6c6df/ : SUCCESS in 5m 43s'}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2015-12-07 17:52:42.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 6: Code-Review+1

Andreas, we've got several co-gates that are not interesting to clog up the integrated gate with, e.g. lbaas, that vote just in check. Is that not allowed?

Sean, given that we're talking about supporitng lb as a first-class citizen, I'd be inclined to think this one *should be* in the gate."}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2015-12-07 17:57:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 6:

Doug, it's allowed - but it's an exception and thus a concise decision that should be justified."}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2015-12-07 18:34:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

I agree it should be at the gate in the future. I think right now, I want to get it voting on changes just to Neutron, so that people pay attention to it and that it can block changes from getting in that break LB. Currently reviewers have to manually verify that it passed the LB job.

So basically small baby steps on the way to being a gate job. We had it experimental, then non-voting, now I think voting in just the Neutron space, then the final step being a voting gate job.'}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2015-12-07 19:00:11.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 7.'}, {'account_id': 10980, 'date': '2015-12-07 19:51:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: Code-Review+1

commit_message:
Make client constructor optional

Turns out we know the mapping of service name to constsructor, so we can
try the import for the user without actually importing. Keep the
argument though, because this method should be usable by just about any
random openstack client lib. Also, because backwards compat.

Change-Id: I7e9672e3bf61b8b7b92d55903f4596382f18b515

commit_message:
copy_puppet_logs: manage testrepository.subunit

Puppet CI wants to have testrepository.subunit file in the logdir so we
can monitor the jobs on http://status.openstack.org/openstack-health/
like other projects.
If the file exists, copy it in the right place.

Change-Id: I89cdd9c3aa9add79b77e1bde35b758b4ee64ead1
Depends-On: I70ecc95dad93b79dbf73f6853ff0ef883f07c9fb

commit_message:
change return code and remove microversion info

This is the doc to talk about v2.1 and we should not
add microversion info into it. Also, the return code is
200 instead of 202 for os-virtual-interfaces GET

Partial-Bug: #1515222

Change-Id: I49fc3b84f94953e99a0748bf6db8892e101ec92f

commit_message:
Delete python bytecode before every test run.

This should eliminate the need to clean -x -i to kill pyc files in
your local directory to get tests to pass.

Change-Id: Icb958a994f0864f11b4f4d091826f3530875fe44
Closes-Bug: #1368661

commit_message:
Change return code from 204 to 202

Even conceptually the delete should return 204, current code
returns 202 so we change the doc now and will restore it back
to 204 when code update.

commit_message:
Remove force-down of service api

it's introduced at microversion 2.11 so we should not
mention it in current v2.1 doc, we can re-add it when
microversion doc is ready.

Change-Id: Ibea6a237010f3e7988f7f341681cff8c01f94c3b
Partial-Bug: #1515222

commit_message:
Add release notes from Icehouse to Liberty

This is the new location for release notes, so this patch includes all
release notes available for ironic. Specifically, it:
- adds links to release notes for icehouse, juno, kilo
- updates the liberty release notes to include 4.0.0 - 4.2.1. This is
  basically a copy of the information from
  https://github.com/openstack/ironic/blob/7c1bc82858533b4b7563fedabb84aed8e721b7a6/doc/source/releasenotes/index.rst
  A follow-up patch will update doc/source/releasenotes/index.rst
  to point to these release notes.

Change-Id: I2511e7564673f4306429ad8b017a1706d4db1af9

commit_message:
Split BaseConductorManager from ConductorManager

This is the second patch in a chain of refactoring patches in preparation
for moving to Futurist library. See blueprint futurist for details.

This patch moves common conductor initialization and lifetime code,
and some common conductor methods to a separate class BaseConductorManager.
I expect most of the work in blueprint futurist to touch this class.

Implements: blueprint futurist
Change-Id: If4f018d6e0473e62134a0427a0ad0ea733c10ea4

Juan: Hi. This patch looks reasonable. One thing I'd like to understand is what is the use case for adding this metadata?

Also, would it make sense to go ahead and add role specific version of the metadata parameters? ControllerServerMetadata vs. CephServerMetadata... Perhaps the use case doesn't require role specific settings and if so that is fine. Perhaps just a bit more detail in the commit message about what exactly you'd plan on doing with the single ServerMetadata parameter for the stack."}, {'account_id': 10873, 'date': '2015-11-11 06:56:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Dan: Well, mostly this one was done because this CR can actually be backported. But for the IdM integration we will use a nova hook that requires some metadata to be set in the nodes. So eventually I will pass custom metadata to the controllers. For now though, adding it to all the nodes in the overcloud is sufficient. Eventually I will push a CR that enables passing role-specific metadata, which will be merged with this one through the usage of map_merge; I didn't, however, push that here because that wouldn't be possible to backport. So I decided it was more appropriate to do it in a separate CR."}, {'account_id': 10873, 'date': '2015-11-11 08:11:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Commit message was updated'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-11 08:17:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

commit_message:
Add option to add metadata for the overcloud nodes

Some Nova hooks might require custom properties/metadata set for the
servers deployed in the overcloud, and this would enable us to inject
such information.

For FreeIPA (IdM) integration, there is effectively a Nova hook that
requires such data.

Currently this inserts metadata for all servers, but a subsequent CR
will introduce per-role metadata. However, that was not added to this
because it will require the usage of map_merge. which will block those
changes to be backported. However, this one is not a problem in that
sense.

Change-Id: I98b15406525eda8dff704360d443590260430ff0

commit_message:
Add style to wrap pre tag

At the moment width of pre tag depend on the length of a line in the
contents. Therefore, if a line in the contents is too long, layout
will be collapsed. I added a style  and it was to fit in the area.

Change-Id: I2ae833051dbb3e2d552c5fd1d7c6dc43da7aa1f5
Closes-Bug: #1520049

commit_message:
Remove tempest from zaqar functional job names

The zaqar functional test jobs were previously named
gate-tempest-dsvm-mongodb-zaqar and gate-tempest-dsvm-redis-zaqar
however neither of these jobs actually run tempest. If you look at
the job definition it quite clearly doesn't even install tempest
and instead just runs a gate hook to trigger zaqar's functional
tests. This commit renames the job to not include tempest in the
name to avoid confusion. It also removes these jobs from the tempest
experimental queue since tempest is not being run there is no reason
to run them on any tempest changes.

Change-Id: Ib7bd69599d5286db2acfc891496ac5e6eb872e7a

commit_message:
HACKING: fix edge case with log hints

A log message with _() was not raised as an error, for example:
LOG.info(_('who let the dogs out!')).

This should be:
LOG.info(_LI('who who who who!'))

Change-Id: I040f01b19ff5de00467b80be7399b998534d9a57
Closes-bug: #1522054

commit_message:
Fix Watcher Applier variables in CamelCase

PEP8 standards call for instance variable names to be written
in the same manner as methods, with underscores separating words.
This fix addresses an instance variable  in the DeployPhase class.

As the instance variable seems public, the Java-ish getter and
setter mentioned in the bug report have been removed as well.

Change-Id: I8835315c8cae64665d3ccb321c4066e37a22c467
Closes-Bug: 1522489

@Matt, the patch that you suggested is not directly relevant here.

What we need is deprecation warning for those aliases we have (f.e. 'neutron.openstack.common.notifier.log_notifier'). The plan, as I understood it, is making oslo.messaging to warn on this type of aliases (by matching alias against 'openstack.common.'). Once we min-cap on oslo.messaging release that will trigger the warning message, we may start counting deprecation clocks (6 months+/1 release+) and remove it in the next neutron release.

So the order would be:

- oslo.messaging warns about those aliases;
- we min-cap on the oslo.messaging release;
(wait 6 month)
- remove the aliases."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-28 01:33:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

commit_message:
Set timetable for removal of oslo.messaging.notify.drivers

Icehouse is dead and gone, at least upstream. These special driver
registrations are not tested in the gate-tempest-dsvm-neutron-full job
which means they are also not tested in requirements constraints jobs.

oslo.messaging 2.6.0 broke these already by removing the internal modules,
which was fixed in o.m 3.0.0 with (deprecated) alias modules.

The minimum required version of o.m in mitaka is currently greater than
2.6.1, so we're OK to remove these once stable/mitaka is our oldest
supported branch. So add a TODO to remove these once liberty-eol happens.

Proper configuration for notification drivers happens through the
config file using the oslo_messaging options:

http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.messaging/opts.html

Adds a release note for the deprecation and timetable.

Change-Id: I2c04117b0f531fe3604e74401d0ffd8d8d3dd308
Related-Bug: #1513630

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-12-07 16:57:24.000000000', 'message': "Skip test_volume_boot_pattern due to bug 1464259

test_volume_boot_pattern is failing frequently on the ceph job in the
cleanup routine due to volume deletion taking longer than expected.
This patch skips this test temporarily until I can sort out what's going
on and propose a reasonable solution.

commit_message:
Skip test_volume_boot_pattern due to bug 1464259

test_volume_boot_pattern is failing frequently on the ceph job in the
cleanup routine due to volume deletion taking longer than expected.
This patch skips this test temporarily until I can sort out what's going
on and propose a reasonable solution.

Change-Id: I335706f47300d13c4abfe3deaf85daf094af0b61
Related-Bug: #1464259

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-09 08:17:30.000000000', 'message': 'Implement /NetworkDriver.Join

        This patch implements /NetworkDriver.Join, which goes through the
        following steps:

        1. Find the Neutron port associated with the given EndpointID
        2. Create the veth pair based on the info of the retrieved port
        3. Bind the port to the veth endpoint
        4. Construct the response with the port and return it
        5. Add support ovs VIF bind

        In the process 3, Kuryr executes the binding script specified in the
        config file. Although users can specify any executable script, Kuryr
        includes several default scripts by default.

Change-Id: I35e48183344f4649242981959bb5d7b03cbec22f
'}]
commit_message:
Implement /NetworkDriver.Join

        This patch implements /NetworkDriver.Join, which goes through the
        following steps:

        1. Find the Neutron port associated with the given EndpointID
        2. Create the veth pair based on the info of the retrieved port
        3. Bind the port to the veth endpoint
        4. Construct the response with the port and return it
        5. Add support ovs VIF bind

        In the process 3, Kuryr executes the binding script specified in the
        config file. Although users can specify any executable script, Kuryr
        includes several default scripts by default.

Change-Id: I35e48183344f4649242981959bb5d7b03cbec22f

commit_message:
rebuild release notes when a project is tagged

Adding a tag to a project needs to trigger the release notes build for
that project so the version numbers in the release notes are updated.
Add the appropriate job to the tag queue, so we get both releases and
pre-releases.

Change-Id: Ibd6427db03aacb0005c16b5a56d4531110d0d6b9

commit_message:
Make nav structure in plugin integration tests pluggable

There are 2 possible setups when running integration tests for a
Horizon plugins.

The first setup, which we suggest to be used in gate of *-dashboard
plugins is to get horizon as a dependency of a plugin and the run
integration tests using horizon.conf config file inside plugin
repo. This way plugin augments the location of Horizon built-in Page
Objects with the location of its own Page Objects, contained within
`plugin_page_path` option and the Horizon built-in nav structure with
its own nav structure contained within `plugin_page_structure`. Then
plugin integration tests are run against core Horizon augment with
just this particular plugin content.

The second setup may be used when we need to run integration tests for
Horizon + several plugins. In other words, content from several
plugins is merged into core Horizon content, then the combined
integration tests from core Horizon and all the involved plugins are
run against the resulting dashboards. To make this possible both
options `plugin_page_path` and `plugin_page_structure` have
MultiStrOpt type. This means that they may be defined several times
and all the specified values will be gathered in a list, which is
iterated when running integration tests.

Change-Id: I9cdd048a3085bfd10690b36e8f94382e91b008d0

commit_message:
Use keystoneauth for auth_token fixture

This patch would have been inflight at the same time as the keystoneauth
conversion patch. Now that it has merged we should use keystoneauth for
the token fixture.

Keystoneauth doesn't make @positional public so continue using that from
ksc - we have this dependency still anyway.

Change-Id: Idb04c805a55d23389fe610e11c45f9138ba1c4ff

commit_message:
Add policy driver option for keystone

This option is entrypoint for the policy backend driver
in the keystone.policy namespace.
Adding below parameter:

policy/driver

Change-Id: Ie1b957f18517591a7ecd4635f907d6f56750beb7

commit_message:
Get rid of the Resource.resource_class() method

Now that we have get_class_to_instantiate() and it always returns
TemplateResource (instead of a custom subclass) for template resources, we
can just compare the types of resources directly.

Change-Id: I96275c3ead3ea3565e55b99a8c5a9948eaa15b78
Related-Bug: #1508115
Related-Bug: #1447194
Related-Bug: #1518458

Fix doc defaults for some parameters.

Some doc section contains defaults to undefined. Move to undef
to be consistent with our policy and another docs.

Pratik, This could be an release note entry and should we add entry for under reno for mentioning about it?

Sergey, because I believe that Keystone will provide the id for user to that user and admin only, and no user can't get the id of other user. I think notification is available to all users who are subscribed to the given mq. so exposing the user id in the notification could be a security risk?"}, {'account_id': 13720, 'date': '2015-11-30 16:00:48.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I don't think the notifications are meant to be user facing. AFAIK, they are available only to operators and hence there is no risk in having user-identity information in them."}, {'account_id': 10487, 'date': '2015-11-30 16:11:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

Sure. I refered the wiki https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/SystemUsageData and you may want to update it new attributes. (also heat notification will become different kind of user information than (like user_id, username, user_identity) against the other types which has only user_id. 

so is it ok to provide inconsistent user information across the notifications types?'}, {'account_id': 13720, 'date': '2015-11-30 16:22:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

That's an excellent point. Unfortunately, since we've been using username as user_id in the past, we have to provide some time for users to change the consumers of the notifications to make the required change (and not to break it immediately). Notice that on the wiki page, it is mentioned that user_id contains user identity which is incorrect.


In the future, I believe that we will use userID for user_id so that notification format will be consistent.


Since the current system is incorrect, I don't see a better way to fix it. Please let me know if you have a better suggestion!"}, {'account_id': 13720, 'date': '2015-11-30 16:35:52.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Updated https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/SystemUsageData'}, {'account_id': 10487, 'date': '2015-12-01 09:21:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2

sure. Fine with this approach, should we create a bug for it and assign to next release, so that it won't be missed.

Should we add this in the reno or else please get assigned the defect to mitaka-1, which in turn will help to get into release notes, i believe."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-12-07 14:02:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

[{'created': '2015-11-30 17:46:18.000000000', 'message': "NetApp cDOT multi-SVM driver can't handle duplicate addresses

When operating in DHSS==True mode, the cDOT driver can receive
separate Neutron subnets for different tenants with overlapping
IP address ranges.  This is typically seen in Tempest testing,
and it is likely to occur for production clouds as well.  VLAN
segmentation is insufficient by itself to resolve the problem.
Starting with 8.3, clustered Data ONTAP supports IPspaces,

commit_message:
NetApp cDOT multi-SVM driver can't handle duplicate addresses

When operating in DHSS==True mode, the cDOT driver can receive
separate Neutron subnets for different tenants with overlapping
IP address ranges.  This is typically seen in Tempest testing,
and it is likely to occur for production clouds as well.  VLAN
segmentation is insufficient by itself to resolve the problem.
Starting with 8.3, clustered Data ONTAP supports IPspaces,
which allow different storage virtual machines (i.e. share
servers) to utilize overlapping address spaces.  This commit
resolves the issue on cDOT 8.3 by creating a new IPspace for
each unique tenant network segment (i.e., each Neutron subnet)
it encounters while creating share servers. It also includes
some minor improvements to error handling when vservers aren't
created and configured successfully plus some trivial refactoring
in the vserver creation path.

Closes-Bug: #1491384
Change-Id: I808547c7d38e6bb61ae10ecdb174d3ab52b1443a

Add network-isolation env file for docker

Add network-isolation support for containerized compute node.

commit_message:
Add template that supports network isolation with docker

This template will configure neutron-agents to run with network isolation
on the containerized compute node.

Change-Id: Ib183a92bd40b7c7eedd8e36ff83593dc828280f4

commit_message:
Add keymgr/encryption_auth_url parameter to cinder API

This value defaults to http://localhost:5000/v3, which works for many
deployments, but if Keystone is located on a separate node,
cinder quota-show $PROJECT_ID fails to contact keystone.

More info about this bug at LP #1516085
Partial-Bug: #1521640

Change-Id: I3457e60e8ce5f2df0830b45c3d18caa88e40f040
(cherry picked from commit 277232eba38ec493bb8d97ad49b2e86457f81fdb)

[{'created': '2015-11-02 19:45:45.000000000', 'message': 'Scaling backup service blueprint spec

Currently the cinder backup service is tightly coupled to the cinder
volume service in ways that prevent scaling out backup services
horizontally across multiple physical nodes.

Here we propose loosening this coupling to enable backup processes
to run on multiple nodes without having to be colocated with volume
services.

Implements: bp scalable-backup-service

Change-Id: I6c56084c82b1d6cd4044e4531ae250a71a1ce16a

commit_message:
Scaling backup service blueprint spec

Currently the cinder backup service is tightly coupled to the cinder
volume service in ways that prevent scaling out backup services
horizontally across multiple physical nodes.

Here we propose loosening this coupling to enable backup processes
to run on multiple nodes without having to be colocated with volume
services.

Implements: bp scalable-backup-service

Change-Id: I6c56084c82b1d6cd4044e4531ae250a71a1ce16a
Co-Authored-By: LisaLi <xiaoyan.li@intel.com>

commit_message:
Add checks for unscoped token data creep to tests

Previously, the assertValidUnscopedTokenResponse method only ensured specific
attributes were in the token response. These checks didn't ensure that the
token scope never grew.

This change makes it so that the assertion will fail if extra attributes are
added to the token response. This should help us be more aware of changes that
have token response data creep by building the check into the tests.

Change-Id: I047421619cc7c8d603b531f6d8de60b54e6826a1
Partial-Bug: 1224273

commit_message:
Add complementary remove lock with prefix function

It seems we provide (and projects use) the provided decorator
'synchronized_with_prefix' but we don't provide an equivalent function
to complement that function to clean up its created lock files.

Providing a complementary method seems pretty useful for projects
that actually clean up these lock files (if any actually do in the
first place).

Change-Id: I601ce3992411e6a2ddded13aba4ac068cf8f14e2

commit_message:
Allow many-to-one glob mapping in registry

This allows mapping several resource type to a single type in the
resource registry.
Mostly useful for testing (map many to OS::Heat::None).
Needed to improve the heat-templates gate.

Change-Id: I5b56c71b5575b73432b0e24df1dc8f8402c17a0c
Closes-Bug: #1499748
Related-Bug: #1492942

commit_message:
Add cross-deps entries for top-role-compute task

This patch introduce an initial change for task.yaml
syntax according to task-based deployment spec:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/245191/

blueprint: task-based-deployment-astute

Change-Id: Icb170d4c38b7c0d9cefc74a5bc7d1d0178ca0bac

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

Hi Giulio,

>I wonder if you think it's valid to remove the for loop as well?
This loop can be useful if you want get several vms. Maybe an other script use this functionality. 

> and if you want to address that in this change?
I can, but I would prefer an atomic commit. If an other script use the ability to have a list of mac. I don't want to include a bug.

It's sure this script must be rewrite. I can prepare and test a commit to do it. 

However if you think it is better to do all in this commit, your are a better view of me, and I will do without hesitate :)"}, {'account_id': 6796, 'date': '2015-12-07 16:23:45.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

commit_message:
Add quoting variable for vnname.

The script can be call with quoted param.
It's mandatory to get the mac of only one vm.
example: tripleo get-vm-mac " instack-server "

Change-Id: I3168c2c63c2d87aa243ab819b9977ec659721026

commit_message:
Serialize cwd in generic task parameters

Astute requires "cwd" task parameter to be
present for certain puppet tasks.
It causes a failure when puppet task is
serialized by generic serializer.

Change-Id: I6c95f99ef2e6079015677c4b937c4e031a0f0809
Partial-Bug: #1521929

commit_message:
Update JS dependencies to fix various bugs

- Update 'ip' to fix issue with Safari
- Update webpack to fix sourcemaps generation with uglifyjs
- Remove uglifyjs - it's a webpack dependency and shouldn't
  be used directly

Change-Id: I01a0afbaeb00dfa67bcdca33764744428dc6cc52
Closes-Bug: #1519784
Partial-Bug: #1517028

commit_message:
Blacklist intel_rapl if running VirtualBox

VirtualBox improperly exposes PAE/NX features, which
causes intel_rapl to report errors to console. This does
not apply to VMs anyway, so it can be disabled.

Change-Id: I29492ffb191b2388be5016c9823e0b2efad9da05
Closes-Bug: #1523526

commit_message:
Add puppet log destination to container start.sh scripts

Added --logdest /var/log/puppet/CONTAINER.log for
each container that runs puppet (excluding rsync and
rsyslog, which do not require a second puppet run).

Change-Id: I013088c89cda5d746043922e23d1d91645779296
Closes-Bug: #1523543

commit_message:
Use yum-builddep from chroot but not from build host

Start using yum-builddep from chroot:
1. Prepare chroot from upstream mirrors only for installing yum inside it
2. Update yum.conf with mos mirrors with path related to chroot
3. Mount local_mirror into chroot
4. Use all yum stuff from chroot

Closes-bug: #1522607

Change-Id: Ifd9d7c6a35c4977e78eba10ffcd0b1a8dcfee4ca

commit_message:
Remove py26 support

As of mitaka, the infra team won't have the resources available to
reasonably test py26, also the oslo team is dropping py26 support
from their libraries. sine we rely on oslo for a lot of our work,
and depend on infra for our CI, we should drop py26 support too.
Closes-Bug: 1519510

Change-Id: I7b202a5baa6e9520827022a545ffafa58578ddcd

The main reason controllers was loaded before kuryr.common.config was imported, was kuryr/__init__.py imported kuryr/controllers.py. So from kuryr.common import config first loads kuryr, that is controllers in it, and then finally loads kuryr/common/config.py.

So as the workaround for this, we can remove "from kuryr.controllers import app" and use app imported from "kuryr.controllers", which imports "kuryr.app". I know this is quite confusing and please see the following patch to see what I'm saying. You can see the following result:

      (kuryr)/Users/tfukushima/py/kuryr% PYTHONPATH=. python scripts/run_server.py --config-file etc/kuryr.conf

      kuryr.server
      kuryr.common.config

commit_message:
Completing the basic configuration for Kuryr

Adds support for providing a configuration file
for specifying Kuryr configuration options.

Updates the Kuryr scripts to use and if needed,
generate the configuration file.

Implements: blueprint kuryr-config
Change-Id: I6909ef21da13a7137ffff019383be19306f35152

Hmmmmm, I guess we can decide the behavior here, and work from that, at least with kazoo it goes the way of what the threading module does, where if u create a lock, u must then use that lock among all users to lock on it. Going by name I think makes sense, and we might just need to do special stuff to handle that (especially in the zookeeper case); the weird part that IMHO becomes odd is the following:

    >>> from tooz import coordination
    >>> c = coordination.get_coordinator("zake://", "me")
    >>> c.start()
    >>> a = c.get_lock("a")
    >>> a.acquire()
    True
    >>> 
    >>> c_2 = coordination.get_coordinator("zake://", "me2")
    >>> c_2.start()
    >>> a_2.acquire()
    >>> (blocks here)

Two coordinators, even using the same name do follow the behavior of the threading module, so going by name would only be useful if the same coordinator is used, which then makes this operate in 2 modes, if u get the lock of the same name from the same coordinator u get the initial lock object (the object used in a prior call to get_lock), if u get a different coordinator and get the lock of the same name, u get a different lock object.

I'd almost prefer just sticking to one way which is get_lock(name) always returns a new object, and if u already acquired that lock of the same name and u try to get the same lock again and acquire it then it will block...

That behavior feels more consistent with the threading module and doesn't try to much to compensate for people doing dumb things (they should know how to track the locks they are using, otherwise they are in for a bad time, and if u find such people, let me know so I can avoid using there code/app...)

my 2 cents :-P'}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2015-11-26 15:17:24.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2015-11-26 15:17:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
lock: make sure all drivers have the same behavior

Currently, all drivers do not have the same behaviour on acquire/release
of their lock based on the name. The test implemented in this patch put
that into the light.

Change-Id: I284bacb83f965e4af8c74ef16cbc74bca8ae8342

commit_message:
Remove py26 from tox.ini and setup.cfg

As of http://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/python3 Openstack
is targeted for py27 and py34 and also dropping py26
for OpenStack mitaka. So In this patch I removed the py26
and added py33 and py34

Change-Id: Ia18f5a5b7255e8df3809f44d0d4c4eaa00adb02d
Closes-Bug: #1523188

commit_message:
DRAC: support for RAID via vendor_passthru

The patch adds support for RAID configuration via the vendor_passthru
interface. The following low level operations are supported:
- listing RAID controllers
- listing virtual disks
- listing physical disks
- creating a single virtual disk
- deleting a single virtual disk
- applying pending RAID configuration
- deleting pending RAID configuration

The methods in ironic.drivers.modules.drac.raid are implemented in a way
that they will also be used by the generic RAID interface. The benefit
of exposing them via vendor_passthru is that the user have more
flexibility for RAID configuration.

The patch also provides way to check the status of the configuration job
created on the DRAC card, since the changes are applied asynchronously.
With these methods the user can follow the progress of the RAID
configuration.

Change-Id: Ic2e255ea2bccc48f41e5f8368ac2c5b6eb345950

commit_message:
Add detail view for bay

This patch adds detail view for bay into bay panel.
Detail view is linked from bay table view and other panel.

Information of Nova instances will be implemented by other patch.
That needs new API that provides instance IDs from bay info.

This patch is with reference to the following patch.
- https://review.openstack.org/173885/

Change-Id: I92078deec23acb349a08362ad9f73feb6bfea22c
Partially Implements: blueprint bay-detail-view

commit_message:
Fix PROJECTS in bgpvpn bagpipe job definition

PROJECTS need to include networking-bagpipe, or else
the enable_plugin ... networking-bagpipe fails.

Change-Id: I2e20c9f6430e28c2f306b9bde74a55ecd8ec9524

commit_message:
Use keystoneauth instead of keystoneclient

keystoneauth was split out last cycle as a library specifically to deal
with doing auth functions so that people who do not need to do keystone
CRUD operations can just consume only the auth session parts. As part
of modernizing keystone interactions, use keystoneauth instead of
keystoneclient.

Depends-On: I1f754a9a949ef92f4e427a91bbd1b1e73e86c8c4
Change-Id: Ia6fb7d8bb07d3101cf1b1afc318f3dcac0a37afc

commit_message:
DVR: only notify needed agents on new VM port creation

When a new VM which should be serviced by a DVR router appears
on compute host, this router is scheduled to that host and
notification is sent. Before the patch it was a broad notification
while really we only need to notify agent on target host.
This should decrease the load on neutron server at scale.

Conflicts:

	neutron/db/l3_dvrscheduler_db.py
	neutron/tests/functional/services/l3_router/test_l3_dvr_router_plugin.py

Closes-Bug: #1486795
Change-Id: Id48b6f6a71530c4f6092d2a07b2db1a5cd300c05

commit_message:
Add MAAS Metric for rabbit queue length

* Adds metrics:
   * notification_messages
   * msgs_excl_notifications
* Adds threshold and rate alarms for msgs_excl_notifications
* Refactors the rabbitmq plugin to reduce duplicated code

Closes #633
Trello: https://trello.com/c/widYAV5F/35-add-new-monitor-rabbitmq-queue-length

Change-Id: Idafbbb150a761d62c8e1dc4c4900ee351993dd5e

commit_message:
Add patch to properly get all commands from dist

Distribution().get_command_list() is not hooked by setuptools like
print_commands() is, as such we do not get a complete command list.

Here we perform the hook ourselves to prevent the need to depend on
a super new version of setuptools.

Change-Id: Ie6088aedb92713be4b8b9af4a4ce3d300a114d7b

commit_message:
Add simple helper function for client construction

Often times you don't want to take advantage of all the flexibility, you
simple want the basic works-like-it-should thing. Add a warpper around
get_legacy_client to do tht one thing.

Change-Id: I086dc4a8e762d4e8e56e01cabe2386577f2ceec8

commit_message:
Add method for registering argparse options

keystoneauth knows about a bunch of argparse options that users
from a command line will want. We do a good job of processing them
once they've been collected, but an os-client-config user doesn't
have a great way to make sure that they register all of the options,
especially when once considers that you really want to peek at the
args to see which auth plugin has been selected so that the right
arguments can be registered and displayed.

Depends-On: Ifea90b981044009c3642b268dd639a703df1ef05
Change-Id: Ic196f65f89b3ccf92ebec39564f5eaefe8a4ae4b

commit_message:
Add Monasca to the Kilo deliverables

All the Monasca components were already tagged with the 2015.1 tag
for the Kilo release. This patch adds them to the deliverables list
for the Kilo release.

Monasca Python Client does not have a launchpad yet so this needs
to be addressed before it can be added.

Change-Id: I586ac2b32b8d21ed61c24f20e431fb479e0f3fa3

commit_message:
Remove references to puppet-openstack from README

The README references to the retired puppet-openstack module
should be removed, as they link to the empty github page.

Change-Id: I064367ed0d5313de300c31863919f64a770148f0
Closes-bug: #1518589

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 455, 'date': '2015-12-07 14:20:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7:

I'm a little concerned about this change.

It changes the documented API:

 http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-image-v2.html

 "If no image data exists, the call returns the HTTP 204 status code. "

I'm also not convinced that it fixes bug 1472449.

The client doesn't handle a 403 response and actually stack traces (you can see this if you run with --debug):

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/mnt/sam/git/python-glanceclient/glanceclient/shell.py", line 605, in main
    args.func(client, args)
  File "/mnt/sam/git/python-glanceclient/glanceclient/v2/shell.py", line 278, in do_image_download
    body = gc.images.data(args.id)
  File "/mnt/sam/git/python-glanceclient/glanceclient/v2/images.py", line 194, in data
    resp, body = self.http_client.get(url)
  File "/mnt/sam/git/python-glanceclient/glanceclient/common/http.py", line 285, in get
    return self._request('GET', url, **kwargs)
  File "/mnt/sam/git/python-glanceclient/glanceclient/common/http.py", line 277, in _request
    resp, body_iter = self._handle_response(resp)
  File "/mnt/sam/git/python-glanceclient/glanceclient/common/http.py", line 93, in _handle_response
    raise exc.from_response(resp, resp.content)
HTTPForbidden: 403 Forbidden: The requested image is in status queued. Image data download is forbidden. (HTTP 403)
403 Forbidden: The requested image is in status queued. Image data download is forbidden. (HTTP 403)

Any other code written against the API will still expect the documented 204.

Also, on line 215 we can still return a 204 (no content) to the client:

raise webob.exc.HTTPNoContent(explanation=e.msg)

so the exact condition in bug 1472449 can still happen (it's just less likely).

I'm wondering if we should:

1) revert this change
2) work on this client side fix https://review.openstack.org/#/c/199549 -- with the addition of correctly handling 200/204/403/other responses.'}]

Fix error when downloading image status is not active

Added check image_status when downloading image.

Change-Id: I39d49ea8a828863fdf4d5efc98126a9009e4b098
Closes-bug: #1472449

commit_message:
Add parameters for Neutron QoS support

Quality of Service advanced service is a feature introduced in Liberty.
This patch adds options required for this service deployment:
- ml2-ovs extensions (to use qos extension)
- ml2-sriov extensions (to use qos extension)
- ml2 plugin extension_drivers (to use qos extension driver)
- qos notification drivers

Change-Id: Iefc289a6eee13b9c66f8131c258af982f232df4b
(cherry picked from commit eaf2f39b904fba951452997deede6319d9ebcebe)

commit_message:
Remove references to puppet-openstack from README

The README references to the retired puppet-openstack module
should be removed, as they link to the empty github page.

Change-Id: I96b8ab38f772aec1fecef18aa016c5a19a5c3532
Closes-bug: #1518589

commit_message:
Remove references to puppet-openstack from README

The README references to the retired puppet-openstack module
should be removed, as they link to the empty github page.

Change-Id: I1e4f5fd79c285b6d7e11eed9619ea26c495798c5
Closes-bug: #1518589

commit_message:
add extras specification for dependencies of dogtag

Add an "extras" list for the dogtag plugin and update tox.ini to
include it. The regular requirements for the package are brought in
automatically, so we don't need requirements.txt to be listed at all.

This dependency list doesn't appear to be complete, because the plugin
still doesn't work, but it demonstrates what could be done and someone
else can take over this patch and complete it if they know the rest of
the needed packages.

Change-Id: Id48bedb2df7ee37de2af2fd85bb7ce0d474c63bf

I think it's a little confusing to have a page just for certificate plugins ("Setting up Certificate Plugins") and then a page labeled "Configurable Plugins", which sort of implies it's going to be all the plugins, but it's actually only crypto and secret store. Hi Richard,

 - Fixed that spacing, thanks!
 - What do you mean by squashing commits?  This change is fully re-based on master.


When it comes to managing init files I see the user in two buckets.

First,  the user that wants swift to start on its own after reboot - without a puppet run.  This user needs to be sure to remove the ubuntu provided init scripts for example.  Those scripts will attempt to start servers based on the default config files- possibly running invalid server configs. These default files for example /etc/swift/object-server.conf are put in place from the debians.  If those config files arn't there, then no problem.  A user can drop in place an init script like I have for example:

 cat /etc/init/start-swift-all.conf
# This file is managed by puppet
# swift-all - All SWIFT services
#
# The swift-all startup script

description     "SWIFT ALL"
author          "Adam Vinsh <adam.vinsh@twcable.com>"

start on runlevel [2345]
stop on runlevel [016]

script
    exec /usr/bin/swift-init all start
end script



Second, the user that doesn't want swift to start until a puppet run.
They should also probably remove the default init scripts.  They don't have to worry about providing a new one as the swift-init resource type introduced in this change will do that work.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-05-07 22:02:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 18: Verified+1

Thank you for fixing the spacing.

With regard to squashing, when you rebase your commits on master, you have the option of squashing (via 'fixup' for example - https://help.github.com/articles/about-git-rebase/#commands-available-while-rebasing) such that when the change is merged back into master, it will appear as a single logical commit. This makes it cleaner and easier to read the history. It is also possible that you've already done this, and I am just not used to how it is presented via the Gerrit interface.

With regard to the users and manual manipulation of init scripts. I feel like this 'two bucket' view is a little arbitrary. I prefer to group users in a single bucket - users who want a service configured with Puppet to just work. =P

As a user, I would expect the be able to fully manage the configuration of replication through the Puppet interface, or for it to be an entirely out-of-band process from Puppet. That is really the core issue I have.

Would it be reasonable to set all pre-canned Swift services to 'ensure => stopped' and 'enabled => false' and then build a new set of services where everything is via swift-init (as you have done with the replicator service)?

If we can get this sorted out, I will be super happy - this is great functionality. Thanks!"}, {'account_id': 11176, 'date': '2015-05-11 18:22:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 18:

I will introduce the "swift_service" defined type as the core of puppet-swift as it is on master.  This involves removing the OS specific service alias and names.  Swift-init allows the control needed on any supported OS.  As is, upstart on Ubuntu is not in good shape with stock debs from UCA.  The init file provided does not provide service status so will fail to restart the proxy service as it currently exists on master.

Once that change has been discussed and accepted, it will be a lot less to review here in this change.

commit_message:
Add support for dedicated replication network.

This change set adds the templates and logic needed
to separate the cluster-internal replication traffic
from the client traffic.  When the replication_network
is enabled and used in concert with the replicate_server
parameter on the server defined type, each conf file
can be individually configured. Swift-init is used
to start server services in pairs.
See also:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/swift/replication_network.html

These changes are meant to be backward compatible with users
that do not want to use a dedicated replication network and
it should not require they make any changes.

It is expected that the user will manage whatever startup
files are required by their OS.  For ubuntu for example,
this involves removing distribution init scripts and replacing
them with a custom script that points at the new conf files.

Change-Id: I90d2390b7ed71eea0eeb724bd5dd0aaa383d7a9d

commit_message:
Python 3: fix cinder.tests.unit.api.v2.test_volumes

dict.iteritems() does not exist in Python 3; use dict.items() instead, since
the performance difference is not overwhelming.

Change-Id: Iaa28405b19e953e47fe7212ce2c3b10973a35c49
Partial-Implements: blueprint cinder-python3

commit_message:
Fixed haproxy backend config issue

The change updates the haproxy configs to use backends with a
default of an empty array. This is needed to ensure that the backends
are not being assumed to have some value. In the current system if an
inventory item did not exist the rendered backend would be a jinja
string which would cause the haproxy play to fail.

Closes-Bug: #1513455

Change-Id: I221dbd910c75c2e41c98a33e1c38c7f69718b544
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
(cherry picked from commit 589650228bb2678487b5750688fe403095955db7)

commit_message:
Creating nova-secret with safe file permissions

This fix will make sure that the nova-secret file will
be created with save "0600" (r--) permissions.

Additionally a new task will make sure that the file is removed
from the filesystem. This will minimize any unprivileged exposure
to the nova-secret file content.

Change-Id: I1c3ec322b2a661cf7dce0334866c90201bbef0a0
Closes-Bug: #1519088
(cherry picked from commit eca0f5ddfba5ac12fc0199d854b3f18504f9ccd3)

commit_message:
Refacter Endpoints into EndpointMap

Because many of the service endpoints URLs use the same patterns for
generating the URLs it makes sense to use the same templates to reduce
the copy and paste.

In the process also adds support for explicitly specifying hostnames
for use in the endpoints.  Note: DNS must be pre-configured.   The
Heat templates do not directly configure DNS.

Change-Id: Ie3270909beca3d63f2d7e4bcb04c559380ddc54d
Co-Authored-By: Juan Antonio Osorio Robles <jaosorior@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Use logging.NullHandler and move Django to requirements

- Adjust requirements with Django module
- Use logging.NullHandler in config
- mark 'test_filter_by_category' and 'test_check_option_switch_env' as
  expected failures, as they're not related to current failure

Co-Authored-By: Victor Ryzhenkin <vryzhenkin@mirantis.com>
Change-Id: I42c1f67f223173c78b0ff1c501bed017855873e0
Closes-Bug: #1522087

commit_message:
Replace HTTP 'magic numbers' with constants

Replace HTTP 'magic numbers' (also known as unnamed numerical constants)
with constants provided by the http_client/httplib library.

For example, use 'http_client.OK' instead of '200'

This was done before in commit 107e064ca1c981480f12fad03fdd02d1f4847422
but a few more HTTP numbers have slipped in since that commit.

Change-Id: Ia3db6b0c8ef832290ffde8510a7ebe33adf356c4

as of mitaka, the infra team won't have the resources available to
reasonably test py26, also the oslo team is dropping py26 support
from their libraries. sine we rely on oslo for a lot of our work,

Closes-Bug: 1519510

commit_message:
Remove py26 support

as of mitaka, the infra team won't have the resources available to
reasonably test py26, also the oslo team is dropping py26 support
from their libraries. sine we rely on oslo for a lot of our work,
and depend on infra for our CI, we should drop py26 support too.

Change-Id: Icf1b13b044de03705688df929ed74429879c6dd8
Closes-Bug: 1519510

commit_message:
Display user's description in user detail

In the case of using keystone v3, user's description is
displayed in user list, but it is not displayed in user
detail. I think we should display just like a user list.

Change-Id: I113a8e5060481b6715acfa936c21ebdc0f4aae29
Closes-Bug: #1522655

commit_message:
security group not mandatory to create instance

as per the nova api and legacy launch instance,
the security group is not mandatory option to create an instance.

but in the new launch instance form, it is marked as
mandatory and it is not allowed to create/launch
an instance if no security group was selected.

this patch making the security group is optional.

Change-Id: Ib381a16922abaf2e704c6a46a8189aec23adfbaa
Closes-Bug: #1501722

commit_message:
Try to avoid intermittent test_dashboard_help_redirection failure

Assuming that the additional browser window is actually opened after
we command test to switch to it, swap these 2 commands. If it doesn't
help, remove the failing test, because ensuring good network
connectivity to external URLs is out of integration tests scope.

Change-Id: I2c972a9ac813f30bb2ea7e6e7d366f729fd90bfb
Related-Bug: #1520582

commit_message:
Do not use empty description fields

When editing the user by the user Update Form
make sure that if the description field has not changed
to not send it, as it will be saved as empty string.
Instead, the value should be absent from the user object,
so it respects the same values as users created in keystone
directly.
Unfortunately, inline editing still triggers the issue
as there is no good way of checking the initial value
without making an extra call.

Change-Id: Id2e0b3c589855068cbc15adc75b57ff0bf61a1b9

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

In case of legacy creds, we only support those on a serial run.

commit_message:
Add network quota exceeding negative test

A quota on the network resource is set. More network resources than
allowed are created. The quota exceeding exception is then catched.

Change-Id: Ic6b846a42276a4cccc0b95fc8654f8c2c16d75c5

commit_message:
Fix to send only one notification when update completes

Presently when an update is COMPLETE/FAILED, two events are reported.

In update_task we are already sending notification when an update
completes, however due to recent changes, notifications are also
sent at the time of releasing stack lock.

For update, we need not send notification when releasing lock.

Change-Id: Idc81f87b143dc43fa5409798534646d8400559ff
Closes-Bug: #1516090

commit_message:
Replace hardcoded port name generation with function

This patch replaces the hardcoded logic for generating the port name
with utils.get_neutron_port_name.

Change-Id: If8275c2c79c3a98cb6adcf436ca779881ac9d1e5
Signed-off-by: Taku Fukushima <f.tac.mac@gmail.com>
Closes-Bug: #1523405

commit_message:
Rework ec2api jobs for new tempest`s plugin technology

Since tempest team implemented plugins and we reworked our ec2api
functional tests to suite tempest`s technology then we can
rework our main gating jobs to use modern way to run functional tests.
But we left old code for stable/kilo branch.

Change-Id: Ib565e1b1095cdafdbe908fe1b1406f57d834fbaa

commit_message:
Remove now duplicate sync;sleep 5

Since https://review.openstack.org/#/c/196252/ merged, nodepool
injects a sync;sleep 5 after running the scripts, so having it in the
scripts is a double sleep.

Change-Id: Ie7a9315e6de67625eca15b45f1662e4c63f8bc10

As of now, I think having both of these job in the experimental queue is fine to start with. I wonder if we can correlate failures between the dvr and the non-dvr case to see if we can go down to a single job (in other words, how likely is it that a breakage in the native support is going to affect only one of the two rather than both)? Running both initially can give us enough data points to make a decision later on.

As for these types of jobs, ultimately we should ask ourselves how many possible combinations of agent (or system) configurations we are actually going to support. The native interface is a natural replacement for the command base one, so once this is proven worthy, we should simply retire these two jobs and flip the switch on the official one.

Doug is right, I have a document that I'll be sending out shortly where I will be proposing best practices and guidelines for job creation and testing targets.

Cheers,
Armando"}, {'account_id': 748, 'date': '2015-12-02 20:23:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 28:

commit_message:
Add job for the ovs mechanism driver with native mode

The ovs mechanism driver recently gained "native" of_driver, which
isn't tested in tempest jobs.
This change adds the job for the ovs driver with interface of native mode.

These jobs are put in the experimental queues.
(We will put them in a periodic queues if they are stable.)

Change-Id: I240e6a60e77ca8fa3b87ec856c65550a3964161e

commit_message:
Use Fedora 23 for Barbican's Dogtag job

The setup in Fedora 21 is broken due to some package issues. On the
other hand, Fedora 21 will be EOL soon. So upgrading to Fedora 23 is the
best step in the long run.

Change-Id: I77fa548e4bc96682808d3721bc5528e091871b6a

Rob, join us in #openstack-infra..'}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2015-12-07 10:06:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Rob, we have two ways to translate code:

* The way the python projects are setup (a single file to translate in $REPOSITORY/locale/$REPOSITORY.pot)
* Horizon and friends with invoking run_tests.sh

I checked out an old version of the repo and see now your changes.

So, "python setup.py extract_messages" should create a file
horizon-cisco-ui/locale/horizon-cisco-ui.pot - and then no need to modify our scripts.

Please move the pot file - like it's done for all python projects, check for example the oslo ones...'}, {'account_id': 12826, 'date': '2015-12-07 10:53:43.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 6547, 'date': '2015-12-07 10:54:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2

commit_message:
Add translation to Cisco UI

The Cisco UI repo contains code that was previously part of core Horizon
and translated. We would like to continue keeping this UI code
translated now that it exists as a Horizon plugin.

Depends-On: I37dee01ae1cd581daf435889689c899d0dafd192
Change-Id: I9de46d899f667a8b7c5cdbfdd965257efae9abd9

commit_message:
Create experimental job for pep8/docs constraints LB

For the neutron-lbaas create a pep8-constraints and a docs-constraints
job as experimental, so that project support for these new jobs can be
tested.

Separate commits will be done for neutron-fwaas and neutron-vpnaas.

Change-Id: Ic2f9bc047f886bf2f9a4646e7f39f3b71f0cfc79
Partial-Bug: #1522503

commit_message:
Updated container_images path

The change updates the image path to use the new pathing instead
of the symlink. This should ensure future usablility of a Juno
based deployment.

Change-Id: Ib041eec44d288d0afee6bbe01feb86d032c1c0d4
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Use WARNING style for JJB compare XML job failure

First word of the job status message to Gerrit will be used to
construct the style to be applied. Using 'WARNING' will activate the
result_WARNING style to be applied from the Gerrit site style sheet.
This should in turn colour the word 'WARNING' differently to ensure it
is easily detectable when the output differs between runs.

Change-Id: Ie7c02c897c48e434f59f530f46d00e3291ea2ef6
Depends-On: I1a9bea0c0830f9ca15f8369632ff2fdbeadada56

commit_message:
Disable reundant neutron services on CI workers

- Disable reundant neutron services on CI workers because its
unused by devstack installation.
Devstack on worker using CI lab resources, where we have neutron
deployed. Accorditg that it's not needed to deploy neutron
services on worker.

Change-Id: I31559127a2a41612ae8653d42fe26f0eddd27f0a

commit_message:
Ability to define the mtu globally (for all the container networks)

Currently, deployers can override MTUs on a per-network basis,
but may be looking for a way to define the mtu globally.

This implements a variable named ``lxc_container_default_mtu``
that currently defaults to 1500 (standard value). If this variable
is set, it will globally override the mtu, while still keeping the
per-network override.

Change-Id: Ia7e4f9e929f513ddc09e6de9467ec6ff765e2e6f
Closes-Bug: #1518311

commit_message:
Change error notification for unknown nodes fail

Before, notification was "Deployment has failed. Check these nodes:
Unknown error".

Now it is more comprehensible. Information about failed nodes is coming
in one of next tasks, so we let the user know that.

Change-Id: I0f397b37747ba654823a819cc957ff6fad450ba1
Partial-Bug: #1506008

commit_message:
Remove dependency on neutron for topics

FWaaS uses L3_AGENT and FIREWALL_PLUGIN topics. The latter is only
used in FWaaS, and can be removed from neutron later.

The goal here is to chip away at removing dependencies on the neutron
repo. This is just one simple case to clean up some unneeded references.

Placed the literals in a new file, which can be used for storing other
constants, as desired.

Change-Id: Idcfeee6ddc2982fff49f44064c918bfd4627be12
Implements: blueprint neutron-lib

commit_message:
reset_stack_status thread_lock needs stack_id

The initial backport of I1739ccbdf75af35aac5be16b99200975df58b8e2 failed
to take into account the different method arguments required by the
thread_lock method, so reset_stack_status doesn't work without this
change.

Change-Id: Id11cf0c7d651433cb8331a20552435fbbf822f92
Closes-Bug: #1514615

commit_message:
Replace which with type in update_modules.sh

which command may not exist in CentOS 7 minimal. 'type -P' is bash
builtin which allows to get full path to binary with proper exit code

Implements: blueprint master-on-centos7

Change-Id: I19ff3ba86da9fb688556161c0413d2d7bc3687c4

commit_message:
Replace which with type in update_modules.sh

which command may not exist in CentOS 7 minimal. 'type -P' is bash
builtin which allows to get full path to binary with proper exit code

Implements: blueprint master-on-centos7

Change-Id: I19ff3ba86da9fb688556161c0413d2d7bc3687c4

commit_message:
Stop to configure 'NameVirtualHost' parameter for apache2

This 'NameVirtualHost' parameter has no effect
and will be removed in the next release of Apache2.

If set '$ip_based' to true, it will prevent from configuring
template with 'NameVirtualHost' parameter:
https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-apache/blob/1.6.0/manifests/vhost.pp#L351-L355
https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-apache/blob/1.6.0/templates/namevirtualhost.erb

Change-Id: Ida886aff947d4074626febc9c52bcccde9eaa36a
Closes-bug: #1484856
